==References== * Akamatsu, Paul. (1972). ''Meiji 1868: Revolution and Counter-Revolution in Japan'' (Miriam Kochan, translator). New York: Harper & Row. * [[William G. Beasley|Beasley, William G.]] (1972). ''The Meiji Restoration.'' Stanford: Stanford University Press. * [[:en:Albert M. Craig|Craig, Albert M.]] (1961). ''Chōshū in the Meiji Restoration.'' Cambridge: Harvard University Press. * [[:en:Marius Jansen|Jansen, Marius B.]] and [[:en:Gilbert Rozman|Gilbert Rozman]], eds. (1986). ''Japan in Transition: from Tokugawa to Meiji.'' Princeton: [[Princeton University Press]]. {{ISBN|9780691054599}}; [https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/12311985 OCLC 12311985] * Jansen, Marius B. (2000). ''The Making of Modern Japan.'' Cambridge: [[:en:Harvard University Press|Harvard University Press]]. {{ISBN|9780674003347}}; [https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/44090600 OCLC 44090600] *Shiba, Ryotaro. (1998). ''The Last Shogun: The Life of Tokugawa Yoshinobu''. Tokyo: Kodansha. {{ISBN|1-56836-246-3}}
]]
